<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no" />
    <meta name="description" content="Legs Exercises" />
    <meta name="author" content="" />
    <title>GymBro - Legs</title>
    <!-- Favicon-->
    <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="assets/favicon.ico" />
    <!-- Core theme CSS (includes Bootstrap)-->
    <link href="/css/styles.css" rel="stylesheet" />
    <style>
        .exercise p {
            font-size: 18px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            margin-top: 20px;
            color: #333;
        }

        .exercise iframe {
            margin-top: 20px;
        }

        .back-button {
            background-color: black;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }

        .back-button:hover {
            background-color: #333;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body style="background-color: #FF9989;">
    <!-- Navigation -->
    <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark">
        <div class="container">
            <a class="navbar-brand" href="/">GymBro</a>
            <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#navbarSupportedContent" aria-controls="navbarSupportedContent" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle navigation"><span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span></button>
            <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarSupportedContent">
                <ul class="navbar-nav ml-auto">
                    <%for(let i=0; i<nav.length; i++) {%>
                        <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link px-lg-3 py-3 py-lg-4" href="<%=nav[i].link%>"><%=nav[i].title%></a></li>
                    <% } %>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <!-- Back Button -->
    <div class="text-left mt-3 ml-3">
        <button class="back-button" onclick="goBack()">Back</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Title -->
    <div class="text-center mt-2">
        <div style="display: inline-block; background-color: white; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);">
            <h1 style="font-family: 'Arial Black', sans-serif; font-size: 3em; color: #333;">Legs</h1>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Page Content-->
    <section class="exercises-section mt-5">
        <!-- Exercise 1 -->
        <div class="exercise">
            <h2>Exercise 1: Squats</h2>
            <p><strong>Target:</strong> Quadriceps, Hamstrings, Glutes</p>
            <div class="rating">Difficulty: ★★★★☆</div>
            <iframe width="100%" height="400" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/PPmvh7gBTi0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            <p>
                Squats are a fundamental lower body exercise that engages multiple muscle groups, including the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. 
                They help in improving overall lower body strength, enhancing core stability, and are beneficial for functional movements in daily life.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Exercise 2 -->
        <div class="exercise mt-5">
            <h2>Exercise 2: Lunges</h2>
            <p><strong>Target:</strong> Quadriceps, Hamstrings, Glutes</p>
            <div class="rating">Difficulty: ★★★★☆</div>
            <iframe width="100%" height="400" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/LCWWq3Lx2Sk" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            <p>
                Lunges are another excellent exercise for targeting the quadriceps, hamstrings, and glutes. 
                They help improve balance, coordination, and core stability, making them a versatile exercise for leg strength and conditioning.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Exercise 3 -->
        <div class="exercise mt-5">
            <h2>Exercise 3: Calf Raises</h2>
            <p><strong>Target:</strong> Calves</p>
            <div class="rating">Difficulty: ★★☆☆☆</div>
            <iframe width="100%" height="400" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/fOfPwmb5FXU" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            <p>
                Calf raises primarily target the calf muscles, aiding in strengthening and toning the lower leg. 
                They are essential for improving ankle stability and can help prevent injuries related to the lower leg and foot.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- JavaScript for Back Button -->
    <script>
        function goBack() {
            window.history.back();
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
